00:32:12.557 --> 00:32:13.390
Price ceiling maybe.

00:32:17.770 --> 00:32:21.420
Oh, you want them to raise
prices to bring in entry?

00:32:21.420 --> 00:32:26.620
Yeah, ooh, ooh, that could
be really expensive, right?

00:32:26.620 --> 00:32:31.390
Remember, if you split,
you've raised costs.

00:32:31.390 --> 00:32:33.070
And now you're going
to raise the price

00:32:33.070 --> 00:32:36.460
to make sure that you can
survive with higher costs.

00:32:39.020 --> 00:32:40.340
You get more companies in.

00:32:43.390 --> 00:32:46.300
There actually have been
examples of competing

00:32:46.300 --> 00:32:48.700
telephone systems historically.

00:32:48.700 --> 00:32:52.220
I don't know of any
competing, I don't

00:32:52.220 --> 00:32:55.970
know offhand of any competing
electric distribution systems.

00:32:55.970 --> 00:32:57.780
There are competing
cable systems.

00:32:57.780 --> 00:32:59.120
It's expensive, right?

00:32:59.120 --> 00:33:00.500
I mean, you're duplicating.

00:33:00.500 --> 00:33:01.880
You're duplicating.

00:33:01.880 --> 00:33:04.370
So most people say, that's
triangles versus rectangles.

00:33:04.370 --> 00:33:07.400
You're saying,
I'll tolerate, I'll

00:33:07.400 --> 00:33:11.720
tolerate a higher cost
as long as they're not

00:33:11.720 --> 00:33:13.620
making any money.

00:33:13.620 --> 00:33:17.190
Well, I don't want to pay a
