00:33:19.740 --> 00:33:22.993
But what you're managing
to do is to raise the cost.

00:33:22.993 --> 00:33:24.660
And that's the natural
monopoly problem.

00:33:24.660 --> 00:33:26.280
That's the core of it.

00:33:26.280 --> 00:33:30.190
If you get competition, then you
will have it at a higher cost.

00:33:30.190 --> 00:33:35.130
And sometimes, if
you think about ways

00:33:35.130 --> 00:33:40.470
that curve could look, sometimes
in fact, if that curve is

00:33:40.470 --> 00:33:44.790
shallow enough, you'd be right.

00:33:44.790 --> 00:33:48.120
Let's have a little competition,
the costs will go up,

00:33:48.120 --> 00:33:50.880
but the incentives
will be stronger.

00:33:50.880 --> 00:33:53.740
They will not hire
their brothers-in-law.

00:33:53.740 --> 00:33:57.360
And yeah, the costs will be up.

00:33:57.360 --> 00:34:00.240
But the pressure on
prices will overwhelm it.

00:34:00.240 --> 00:34:02.940
Mostly that's not true.

