You do see it.

00:34:42.060 --> 00:34:44.530
Let me just mention, there are
a number of different ways.

00:34:44.530 --> 00:34:46.199
Those are the three
main alternatives.

00:34:46.199 --> 00:34:47.699
There are a number
of different ways

00:34:47.699 --> 00:34:49.980
to skin this one, to regulate.

00:34:49.980 --> 00:34:53.565
And I'll just say a little bit,
not go into too much detail.

00:34:57.940 --> 00:35:00.040
Regulation, so I've got
government ownership

00:35:00.040 --> 00:35:02.890
at the top and
cooperatives at the bottom.

00:35:02.890 --> 00:35:05.847
I didn't talk about
franchise bidding.

00:35:05.847 --> 00:35:07.930
I think that will take us
a little too far afield.

00:35:07.930 --> 00:35:13.780
But that's the bid for the
right to provide electricity.

00:35:13.780 --> 00:35:18.700
Different kinds of
regulation, you could do--

00:35:18.700 --> 00:35:22.480
the early streetcars and buses
and electric power systems

00:35:22.480 --> 00:35:25.880
and cable systems were
regulated by cities.

00:35:25.880 --> 00:35:28.010
And the city had
jurisdiction because they

00:35:28.010 --> 00:35:30.490
needed to use the streets.

00:35:30.490 --> 00:35:35.080
So yes, you can put
up your phone lines,

00:35:35.080 --> 00:35:36.790
yes, you can run the streetcars.

00:35:36.790 --> 00:35:41.770
But you need to comply
with certain restrictions.

00:35:41.770 --> 00:35:44.080
I will talk about rate
of return regulation.

00:35:44.080 --> 00:35:47.650
That's been the
dominant way electricity

00:35:47.650 --> 00:35:50.560
has been regulated since
the early 20th century.

00:35:50.560 --> 00:35:54.010
It's focused on profits.

00:35:54.010 --> 00:35:57.910
And incentive
regulation is to try

00:35:57.910 --> 00:36:00.790
to hold prices
constant for a while

00:36:00.790 --> 00:36:04.120
to give incentives to cut cost.

00:36:04.120 --> 00:36:05.770
I will cycle back to this.

00:36:05.770 --> 00:36:06.680
I will cycle back.

00:36:06.680 --> 00:36:09.197
But just to know that there
