00:36:09.197 --> 00:36:10.030
that have been used.

00:36:10.030 --> 00:36:14.270
They all become political.

00:36:14.270 --> 00:36:17.290
They involve decisions
made by people.

00:36:17.290 --> 00:36:19.090
They involve decisions
made by people

00:36:19.090 --> 00:36:23.660
who are subject to voters,
typically, one way or another,

00:36:23.660 --> 00:36:26.770
either government enterprise
or they are regulated

00:36:26.770 --> 00:36:32.050
or the co-op members vote.

00:36:32.050 --> 00:36:34.510
So one of the things you
want to do is as little

00:36:34.510 --> 00:36:36.410
of this as possible.

00:36:36.410 --> 00:36:39.430
So transmission
and distribution,

00:36:39.430 --> 00:36:44.980
natural monopolies
pose a policy problem.

00:36:44.980 --> 00:36:50.610
In terms of the
architecture, I don't know

00:36:50.610 --> 00:36:55.530
why this is a blackboard talk.

00:36:55.530 --> 00:36:59.280
But when I say that low voltage
distribution systems are

00:36:59.280 --> 00:37:03.510
a tree, there will
be a substation

00:37:03.510 --> 00:37:14.880
and feeders go out to serve
neighborhoods and houses

00:37:14.880 --> 00:37:17.190
and so forth.

00:37:17.190 --> 00:37:19.470
The transmission
system, if you look,

00:37:19.470 --> 00:37:21.150
I'll show you a map
in a little bit.

00:37:21.150 --> 00:37:23.130
But you might have
a generator here.

00:37:23.130 --> 00:37:26.430
You might have city or
load here and load there

00:37:26.430 --> 00:37:28.590
and another generator here.

00:37:28.590 --> 00:37:30.660
The transmission
system will be a mesh.

00:37:36.840 --> 00:37:38.828
It's a different architecture.

00:37:38.828 --> 00:37:40.245
It means there are
multiple paths.

00:37:42.900 --> 00:37:46.290
In the tree structure,
you'd have a substation.

00:37:46.290 --> 00:37:48.670
And this would be a house.

00:37:48.670 --> 00:37:50.940
There's only one path.

00:37:50.940 --> 00:37:54.570
There are multiple paths,
well, in this case three

00:37:54.570 --> 00:37:56.520
from this generator
to this load.

00:37:59.610 --> 00:38:03.660
The reason for multiple paths
of course, is reliability.

00:38:03.660 --> 00:38:05.580
The reason for a tree
structure is cost.

00:38:08.460 --> 00:38:12.060
In some dense urban areas,
the distribution system

00:38:12.060 --> 00:38:14.490
is a mesh because
the lines are short.

00:38:14.490 --> 00:38:16.090
And you might as well.

00:38:16.090 --> 00:38:19.290
But if you think of any rural
or suburban area, it's a tree.

00:38:22.860 --> 00:38:26.310
The transmission system, I
have to say for most of us

00:38:26.310 --> 00:38:27.930
it takes a little
getting used to.

00:38:27.930 --> 00:38:31.910
You don't switch current, right?

00:38:31.910 --> 00:38:36.440
If you do the analysis,
power from this generator

00:38:36.440 --> 00:38:42.080
to this load goes
on all three paths,

00:38:42.080 --> 00:38:45.270
depending on the
characteristics of the path.

00:38:45.270 --> 00:38:46.790
You can change those
characteristics

00:38:46.790 --> 00:38:48.620
with expensive technology.

00:38:48.620 --> 00:38:51.470
But mostly it's passive.

00:38:51.470 --> 00:38:57.200
That means-- well,
it means two things.

00:38:57.200 --> 00:39:08.630
That means if I demand more
here, Demand goes up here,

00:39:08.630 --> 00:39:12.710
and I increase generation
here, I could in fact

00:39:12.710 --> 00:39:15.680
cause a problem on this
line because some power

00:39:15.680 --> 00:39:17.490
will flow through it.

00:39:17.490 --> 00:39:20.330
And if that line can't
handle it, I could run into,

00:39:20.330 --> 00:39:21.410
it could overheat.

00:39:21.410 --> 00:39:22.760
It could sag.

00:39:22.760 --> 00:39:24.890
This is called loop flow.

00:39:24.890 --> 00:39:31.820
When electricity over multiple
paths causes problems,

00:39:31.820 --> 00:39:36.530
particularly let's say,
that's a national border.

00:39:36.530 --> 00:39:38.360
So I can cause
congestion over here.

00:39:38.360 --> 00:39:40.970
I can cause a problem
over here when I increase

00:39:40.970 --> 00:39:43.940
demand and generation here.

00:39:43.940 --> 00:39:46.685
Now, you might say,
well, can't we fix that?

00:39:46.685 --> 00:39:47.810
The answer is a little bit.

00:39:47.810 --> 00:39:51.740
We can fix that now
with power electronics.

00:39:51.740 --> 00:39:55.010
We can change some of the
characteristics of these lines.

00:39:55.010 --> 00:39:57.890
But it's expensive,
and it's not much done.

00:39:57.890 --> 00:40:01.760
OK, so it's a strange system.

00:40:01.760 --> 00:40:06.080
It's not intuitive,
not intuitive.

